<li id="cite_note-37"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="Spain#cite_ref-37">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Typical <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aurignacian" title="Aurignacian">Aurignacian</a> items were found in Cantabria (Morín, El Pendo, <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cave_of_El_Castillo" title="Cave of El Castillo">El Castillo</a>), the Basque Country (Santimamiñe) and Catalonia. The radiocarbon datations give the following dates: 32,425 and 29,515 BP.<sup class="noprint Inline-Template" style="white-space:nowrap;">&#91;<i><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Verifiability" title="Wikipedia:Verifiability"><span title="The material near this tag failed verification of its source citation(s). (January 2016)">failed verification</span></a></i>&#93;</sup>[</span>
